Officers stopped a bakkie on Monday morning and discovered the fuel. The pair apparently couldn't explain why they were transporting such a large amount of diesel. CAPE TOWN - Kathu police have arrested two men for being in possession of suspected stolen diesel worth R25,000 in the Northern Cape. Officers stopped a bakkie on Monday morning and discovered the fuel. The pair apparently couldn't explain why they were transporting such a large amount of diesel. They then allegedly tried to bribe the officials. The police's Mohale Ramatseba said: "They will receive an additional charge of bribery and they will appear in court soon."